parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight Flickering and Failure (HID Xenon Headlights)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random failure of the HID xenon headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising the safety of the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The headlights flicker and shut off randomly while driving
sometimes returning to normal operation after shutting off and restarting the vehicle. The issue is more frequent in cold weather and may be exacerbated by vibration or bad roads.
